{% vim:set ft=djot: %}

`djotfmt` will wrap long attributes (both inline and block) to the 72
column width, including comments.

* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *

{ .some-very-very-long-class #some-very-very-long-id % some very very
  long comment % }

> { .some-very-very-very-very-very-very-very-long-class
>   #some-very-very-long-id % some very very very very very very long
>   comment %}

{ key="some very very very very very very very very very very very very
  long value"
  % some very very very vere very very long comment % }

some *text*{ .some-very-very-very-very-very-very-very-long-class % some
very very very very very very long comment %
#some-very-very-very-long-id key="some very very very very very very
very very very very very very long value"}
